refactor(news): flip-card for Dolladille visit tile

The previous implementation (.timeline__item--visual) made the visit
tile span two grid columns, which stretched the adjacent news tiles
to match its height and made the row look anemic. Replaced with an
auto-flipping card that takes exactly one grid column like every
other news tile:

- Front: date, title, and a 3-line clamped body excerpt, plus a
  subtle circular refresh hint in the top-right corner.
- Back: the visit photo, full-bleed with object-fit: cover.
- Both faces share the same grid cell (grid-template-areas: "face")
  so the parent sizes to the larger face; height: 100% lets the grid
  stretch us to the row's natural height.
- 12-second cycle: front visible 0-42%, flip to back at 52%, back
  visible until 92%, flip back to front at 100%. Cubic-bezier easing
  makes the rotation feel decisive rather than mechanical.
- Hover or keyboard focus pauses the flip (animation-play-state).
- prefers-reduced-motion disables the animation entirely; front face
  stays visible with the text content.
- Red border-top on the back + blue border-top on the front echo the
  Franco-Japanese palette used on the other timeline cards.

.claude/launch.json now configured (port 8282) so the preview server
can be reused for subsequent verification.
